# Architecture and Data

- Keep LenDen fully client-side and static-hostable; avoid backend/API dependencies unless explicitly approved.
- Keep `index.html` + `css/styles.css` + `js/app.js` structure intact and use existing `showPage`/`page-*`/`nav-*` patterns.
- Use `LS`/`DB` wrappers for persistence; do not scatter direct localStorage usage in new code.
- Preserve canonical `ld2_*` keys and backward compatibility via migration/normalization, not destructive schema changes.
- Reuse core helpers (`fmt`, `today`, date helpers, deterministic finance calculations) and escape user text with `escHtml`.

# EMI Rules

- Preserve fee/GST settlement model for lending (`chargedAmount`, fee %, flat fee, GST components, settlement).
- Use dedicated `ld2_emi_schedules` for installment planning; keep actual repayments in `ld2_payments`.
- Keep EMI schedule entries pending by default; only confirmed receipts affect transaction paid/due status.
- Protect settled repayment history on edits; do not silently remove already received installments.

# Testing and Delivery

- Add/update `tests/regression.js` for finance/storage/migration behavior changes.
- Maintain smoke coverage in `tests/e2e/smoke.spec.js` for boot and critical repayment flows.
- After substantial edits, run syntax/lint checks and attempt smoke tests when environment permits.
- If runtime prerequisites are blocked (for example Playwright browser install), report blocker and exact local command to run.
- Keep CI/deploy static-first (`netlify.toml` publish root), npm registry pinned to npmjs.org, and Playwright artifacts uploaded on failures.

# Collaboration and Suggestions

- Execute end-to-end where feasible: implement, validate, and summarize.
- Preserve user’s in-progress local changes; avoid reverting unrelated edits.
- If a request is likely suboptimal, still address intent and also suggest 2-3 better alternatives with concise trade-offs.
- Default recommendations should favor simplicity, backward compatibility, data safety, and testability.

# Documentation Maintenance

- Keep `README.md` accurate with current architecture, features, storage model, testing, and upgrade notes.
- Whenever significant enhancements or new features are added, update `README.md` in the same change set.
